      tasks:
      - name: get-coachella-start-date
        template: get-coachella-start-date
      - name: get-weather-forecast
        dependencies: [get-coachella-start-date]
        template: get-weather-forecast

            value: 'Coachella'
          - name: date
            value: '{{ tasks.get-coachella-start-date.result }}'
  - name: get-coachella-start-date
    script:
      image: python:3.8
      command: [python]
      source: |
        # This script should return the start date of the Coachella festival
        import datetime
        # Assuming Coachella starts on the second Friday of April
        today = datetime.date.today()
        year = today.year
        april_first = datetime.date(year, 4, 1)
        # Find the first Friday in April
        first_friday = april_first + datetime.timedelta(days=(4 - april_first.weekday() + 7) % 7)
        # Coachella starts on the second Friday
        coachella_start_date = first_friday + datetime.timedelta(weeks=1)
        print(coachella_start_date)
  - name: get-weather-forecast
    http:
      url: "http://weatherapi.example.com/GetWeatherForecast"
      method: GET
      parameters:
      - name: city
        value: '{{ inputs.parameters.city }}'
      - name: date
        value: '{{ inputs.parameters.date }}'
